text: The Williams Tower (originally named the Transco Tower) is a 64-story, office tower. It is located in Houston, Texas. Construction began in August 1981, and was completed in December, 1982. It is the 4th-tallest tower in Texas, and the 44th-tallest in the United States. ==References== Category:Skyscrapers in the United States Category:Buildings and structures in Houston
title: Williams Tower
